President Obama has declared a major disaster in the state of Minnesota following severe storms and tornadoes that occurred in May 2011. Federal aid will be provided to supplement state and local recovery efforts in Anoka and Hennepin Counties, including funding for emergency work and the repair or replacement of damaged facilities. Hazard mitigation measures will also receive federal funding statewide. Paul J. Ricciuti has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected area. Additional designations for assistance may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, contact FEMA at (202) 646-3272.